Richard V. Werner and his two sons, Richard W. and Charles, formed the plaintiff, a Georgia corporation, in 1940, to conduct business of steel scaffolding rental in the southeast. (During the tax years here in question, Richard W. and Charles were the sole shareholders in plaintiff, the father having died in 1957.)
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
