 The plaintiff, in fact, paid two hundred dollars ($200.00) per month in rent. Under all of the evidence, the Court cannot conclude that the lease of the unimproved real estate for that rental was unreasonable. However, the parties knew then that the property was to be improved by the lessee with a thirty-four (34) year building to revert to the landowners (stockholders) in twenty (20) years. Therefore, the total return to the owners included both the rental plus the reversion reasonably expected.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
